      },
      "type": "term",
      "surface": {
        "jp": "基数",
        "zh": "基数",
        "en": "Radix"
      },
      "definition": {
        "jp": "桁上がりの基準となる数です。10進数は10になるときに桁が上がるので、10進数の基数は「10」です。同様に、2進数の基数は「2」、16進数の基数は「16」です。",
        "zh": "是进位的基准数。十进制在达到10时进位，因此十进制的基数为「10」。同样，二进制的基数为「2」，十六进制的基数为「16」。",
        "en": "It is the number that serves as the standard for carrying. Decimal numbers carry over when they reach 10, so the radix of decimal is \"10\". Similarly, the radix of binary is \"2\" and the radix of hexadecimal is \"16\"."
      },
      "kana_helper": null
    },
    {
      "id": "itpassport_r6::term::p320::1",
      "anchor": {
        "page": 320,
        "block_id": "page_320_block_1",
        "section_path": []
      },
      "type": "term",
      "surface": {
        "jp": "基数変換",
        "zh": "基数转换",
        "en": "Radix Conversion"
      },
      "definition": {
        "jp": "どの表記法であっても、表記が異なるだけで本質的に表している値は同じであり、相互に変換できます。この変換のことを「基数変換」といいます。",
        "zh": "无论采用哪种表示法，只是表示方式不同，本质上所表示的值是相同的，可以相互转换。这种转换称为「基数转换」。",
        "en": "Regardless of the notation, only the representation differs while the value being expressed is essentially the same, and the notations can be converted to each other. This conversion is called \"radix conversion\"."
      },
      "kana_helper": null
    },
